<body style="padding:5%">
    <header class="text-center">
        <div>
            <center>
                <img class="img-responsive" src="http://www.chattahoocheetech.edu/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/the_essentials_new_website_header_revised_1200.jpg" alt="ChattahoocheeTech Banner Picture" width="1200" height="180">
            </center>
            <h3> As an HR employee, you are assigned the task of maintaining employees' weekly timesheets.</h3>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="text-center">

        <h3>General Info</h3>
        <p>
            After a successful login as an HR employee, you will reach a paysheet summaries page.
            Once on the paysheet summaries page, an HR employee can select a week ending date via a drop down tab in the middle
            of the page
            Once a week ending date is selected, employees with timesheets for that date will be listed.
        </p>

        <a class="btn btn-default" href="~/Content/hrdrop.jpg" alt="hrdrop pic" target="_blank"> Example</a>

        <hr>


        <h3>Exporting To Excel</h3>

        <p>
            The option to export a report to excel is also present near the bottom of the page, clicking it will allow the HR employee
            to choose a save location for the excel file.
        </p>

        <a class="btn btn-default" href="~/Content/export1.jpg" alt="export pic" target="_blank"> Example</a>

        <hr>

        <h3>Opening & Editing Timesheets </h3>
        <p>
            Selecting an employee's name and ID will open an overview page that contains the employee's timesheet.
            While viewing the overview page for an employee, you will have the ability to edit the timesheet if there are errors.
            Saving an employee's timesheet information after making changes will send a generated email to that employee.
            If any fields are left blank or have errors, an indicator will pop up to show where changes need to be made.
        </p>

        <a class="btn btn-default" href="~/Content/edit1.jpg" alt="edit pic" target="_blank"> Example 1</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

        <a class="btn btn-default" href="~/Content/edit2.jpg" alt="edit pic" target="_blank"> Example 2</a>

        <hr>

        <h3>Emailing Employees</h3>
        <p>
            There are two ways to email an employee: one method of emailing an employee is by the email section at the bottom of the page,
            the other method is via an email link where the employee's email is displayed.
            Upon clicking on an employee's email on the overview page, an email window will be displayed. Your HR email must be signed in and
            you will be able to compose an email to send to the selected employee.
        </p>

        <a class="btn btn-default" href="~/Content/email1.jpg" alt="email pic" target="_blank"> Example 1</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

        <a class="btn btn-default" href="~/Content/email2.jpg" alt="email pic" target="_blank"> Example 2</a>
        <hr>

        <h3>Printing Timesheets</h3>
        <p>
            An HR employee may be able to print an employee's timesheet via the print button in the overview page. A print window will then pop up
            prompting the user to print to the default printer.
        </p>

        <a class="btn btn-default" href="~/Content/print1.jpg" alt="print pic" target="_blank"> Example </a>
        <hr>
    </main>
</body>
